sources.title: Oliver Twist 1933 (Literary Drama) A Charles Dickens story, Directed by William J. Cowen
sources.description:
From Orphan to Hero: The Timeless Tale of Oliver Twist, the Classic Story of Adventure, Danger, and Redemption!
Oliver Twist, a young orphan navigates the grim streets of London, encountering both kindness and cruelty. As he faces numerous challenges, Oliver's resilience and bravery ultimately lead him to a better life.

Original title: Oliver Twist (1933)
This film is subtitled in many languages.

Colorized version: https://youtu.be/tAZLL5I4ios


Director: William J. Cowen
Writer: Based on the novel by Charles Dickens
Actors: Dickie Moore, Irving Pichel, William 'Stage' Boyd , Doris Lloyd, Alec B. Francis, Barbara Kent
Genres: Classics, Drama, Mystery, Family, Literary
